problem_prompt: Solve the following problem. What is the greatest common divisor of $7979$ and $3713$?
solution:
We can use the Euclidean Algorithm to find the greatest common divisor of these two integers. \begin{align*}
\gcd(7979, 3713) &= \gcd(3713, 7979 - 2\cdot 3713) \\
&= \gcd(3713, 553) \\
&= \gcd(553, 3713 - 6\cdot 553) \\
&= \gcd(553, 395) \\
&= \gcd(395, 553 - 395) \\
&= \gcd(395, 158) \\
&= \gcd(158, 395- 2\cdot 158) \\
&= \gcd(158, 79) \\
&= \boxed{79}.
\end{align*}
gpt_response:

\begin{align*}
7979 &= 2 \cdot 3713 + 553 \\
3713 &= 6 \cdot 553 + 395 \\
553 &= 1 \cdot 395 + 158 \\
395 &= 2 \cdot 158 + 79 \\
158 &= 2 \cdot 79
\end{align*}

Since the remainder is $0$, we stop the algorithm. The greatest common divisor of $7979$ and $3713$ is the last non-zero remainder, which is $\boxed{79}$.
